-- Britain to sell more shares in Lloyds in next 6 months
-- By Matt Scuffham
-- Wed Dec 17, 2014 09:56AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Dec 17 (Reuters) - Britain will sell more shares in Lloyds Banking Group <LLOY.L> in the next six months, the body which manages its shareholding in bailed out banks said on Wednesday.

UK Financial Investments (UKFI), said it would sell the shares through a pre-arranged trading plan that will be managed by investment bank Morgan Stanley.